Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2759/75 of 29 October 1975 on the common organization of the market in pigmeat (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1249/89 (2), and in particular Article 20 thereof,
Whereas, because of the outbreak of classical swine fever in certain production regions in Belgium, which are located in the border area to the Netherlands, animal health measures have been established by the Dutch authorities pursuant to Council  Directive 80/217/EEC of 22 January 1980 introducing Community measures for the control of classical swine fever (3), as last amended by Decision 93/384/EEC (4), and exceptional support measures for the market in pigmeat have been adopted for this Member  State by Regulation (EC) No 1393/94 (5), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 2067/94 (6);
Whereas in view of the progress achieved on the animal health side, the exceptional market support measures can now be closed down; therefore, Regulation (EC) No 1393/94 needs to be repealed;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Pigmeat,
